Cell["\<\
Using the sorted list, we find the order of {p,q} values to be {{3,2}, {5,2}, \
{7,2}, {4,3}, {5,3}, {7,3}, {8,3}, {5,4}, {7,4}, {6,5}, {7,5}, {8,5}, {7,6}, \
{8,7}}.
This suggests that q carries more weight in determining the arc length of the \
knots.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.760469287888894*^9, 3.7604693264647307`*^9}, {
  3.7604693796780653`*^9, 3.7604694006589527`*^9}, {3.7604694399509306`*^9, 
  3.760469634548375*^9}, {3.76046968608055*^9, 
  3.7604697874517264`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"01681930-e40d-4cb5-9101-\
5810df072854"],

Cell["\<\
It appears that p determines the number of arcs and/or intersections of arcs \
on the outside of the knot, where you are viewing the knot in such a way that \
the z axis is coming out of the screen. q determines how many of these \
outward arcs are passed (minus 1) until a segment from one of the arcs exits \
the \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]body\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] of the knot as \
another outward arc. For example, the trefoil knot has 3 \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]outward arcs\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], and a segment \
from on of these arcs exits the knot 2 arcs away, where the trefoil knot has \
p and q of {3,2}.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.760469964543609*^9, 3.76046997863626*^9}, {
  3.760470047351158*^9, 3.76047015456537*^9}, {3.7604702116239414`*^9, 
  3.760470280454705*^9}, {3.7604703114417777`*^9, 
  3.760470428770964*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"91a86497-5430-4361-8415-\
3843b15f8603"]
}, Open  ]]
},
